name: AXError
desc: Error codes returned by accessibility functions.

items.name: case apiDisabled
items.desc: Assistive applications are not enabled in System Preferences.

items.name: case actionUnsupported
items.desc: The referenced action is not supported. Alternatively, you can return the eventNotHandledErr error.

items.name: case attributeUnsupported
items.desc: The referenced attribute is not supported. Alternatively, you can return the eventNotHandledErr error.

items.name: case cannotComplete
items.desc: A fundamental error has occurred, such as a failure to allocate memory during processing.

items.name: case illegalArgument
items.desc: The value received in this event is an invalid value for this attribute. This also applies for invalid parameters in parameterized attributes.

items.name: case invalidUIElement
items.desc: The accessibility object received in this event is invalid.

items.name: case invalidUIElementObserver
items.desc: The observer for the accessibility object received in this event is invalid.

items.name: case parameterizedAttributeUnsupported
items.desc: The parameterized attribute is not supported. Alternatively, you can return the eventNotHandledErr error.
